widgets_values:
Pony Model Guidance from LS582 on CivitAI

score_9, score_8_up, score_7_up, score_6_up, score_5_up, score_4_up
source_pony, source_furry, source_cartoon, source_anime
rating_safe, rating_questionable, rating_explicit

Depending on model; you'll want to use either the whole string of score in positive, or split score 9-7 in positive, and 6-4 into negative. Or just source 9. (Use these tags as they are, with the underscores because that's how the model was trained, but I recommend saving all of that for future reference.) Source tags are internal to the model and que it for more specific kinds of images, you want to use at least one in the positive. ratings aren't explicitly needed, but will direct the model to being safe, questionable, or explicit with the output.
